Open-Source Recycled Plastic Pelletizer:
A mechanical system designed to take shredded plastic waste and extrude it into uniform, high-quality pellets for 3D printing or injection molding.

Features:
- Open-Source: Fully documented CAD models and assembly instructions.

- Modular Design: Easy maintenance and component swapping.

- Adjustable: Variable speed and temperature control for different polymers.

Repository Structure:
- /CAD - 3D models (STEP, STL) and technical drawings

- /Code - Microcontroller and firmware code

- /Electronics - Wiring diagrams

- BOM.csv - Bill of Materials with sourcing links

- /Media - Photos and Videos

Acknowledgements:
Developed for the FAST Lab at Western University under Dr. Alessia Romani.
